libsyspower is a Linux library for managing power state, wakeup sources and power supplies.

== build ==
mkdir build && cd build
cmake ../
make

=== tools/demo ===
```
$ ./syspowerwakesrc list
Device                         HW wakeup
|- 2-0024                      [disabled]
|- 30b10000.usb                [disabled]
|- ci_hdrc.1                   [disabled]
|- 30b20000.usb                [disabled]
|- ci_hdrc.0                   [disabled]
|- 0-0009                      [enabled]
|- 1-0066                      [disabled]
|- 30370000.snvs:snvs-rtc-lp   [enabled]
|- 30370000.snvs:snvs-powerkey [enabled]
prompt: ~/ ./syspowerwakesrc enable 2-0024
prompt: ~/ ./syspowernap 
Sleeping now...
Wakeup! (2-0024/irq:74)
```

```
$ ./syspowersupply monitor
=== BAT0 ===
type: BATTERY
capacity: 97%
status: NotCharging
health: Warm
now: 0mA/12234mV/0mW
connected: yes
=== AC ===
type: MAIN
health: Unknown
connected: yes
```

```
 ./syspowerwakesrc list
Device                         HW wakeup
|- 00:04                       [enabled]
|- alarmtimer.0.auto           [enabled]
|- serio0                      [disabled]
|- serio1                      [disabled]
|- 0000:00:1c.0                [enabled]
|- 0000:04:00.0                [disabled]
|- 1-3.2.4                     [disabled]
|- 1-3.2                       [disabled]
|- 1-3.2.3.3                   [enabled]
|- 1-3.2.3                     [disabled]
|- 1-3.2.3.4                   [disabled]
|- 1-3.2.1                     [disabled]
|- 1-3                         [disabled]
|- usb1                        [disabled]
|- 1-6                         [disabled]
|- 0000:00:14.0                [enabled]
|- 2-4.2.3                     [disabled]
|- 2-4.2                       [disabled]
|- 2-4.2.4                     [disabled]
|- 2-4                         [disabled]
|- usb2                        [disabled]
|- PNP0C0D:00                  [enabled]
|- PNP0C0E:00                  [enabled]
|- PNP0C0A:00                  [enabled]
|- LNXPWRBN:00                 [enabled]
```
